9 An Act relating to the Oklahoma State Bureau of
Investigation; amending 74 O.S. 2021, Section 150.9,
10 as amended by Section 583, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025
(74 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 150.9), which relates to
11 criminal history records; removing obsolete language;
providing time frame for completion of certain record
12 checks; amending fee schedule for certain records;
updating statutory language; updating statutory
13 reference; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 150.9, as
18 amended by Section 583, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (74 O.S. Supp.
19 2025, Section 150.9), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 150.9. A. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation
21 shall procure, file, and maintain criminal history records for each
22 person subject to mandatory reporting as provided by law, including
23 photographs, descriptions, fingerprints, measurements, and other
24 pertinent information relating to such persons. It shall be the
SB1921 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 duty of law enforcement officers and agencies, sheriffs, police,
2 courts, judicial officials, district attorneys, and the persons in
3 charge of any state correctional facility or institution to furnish
4 criminal history records to the Bureau as required by Section 150.1
5 et seq. of this title. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation
6 shall cooperate with and assist the sheriffs, chiefs of police, and
7 other law enforcement officers of the state by maintaining a
8 complete criminal history record on each person subject to mandatory
9 reporting as provided by law, and shall have on file the fingerprint
10 impressions of all such persons together with other pertinent
11 information as may from time to time be received from the law
12 enforcement officers of this and other states or as may be required
13 by law.
14 B. 1. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation is authorized
15 to conduct and receive results of national criminal history record
16 checks for authorized purposes pursuant to Public Law P.L. No. 92-
17 544, the National Child Protection Act/Volunteers for Children Act
18 (NCPA/VCA) as amended, with or without a Volunteer and Employee
19 Criminal History System (VECHS) waiver program or any other federal
20 authorizing statute. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation
21 shall only release the results of national criminal history record
22 checks to entities authorized to receive the results pursuant to
23 federal law.
24
SB1921 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. Any state agency, board, department, or commission or any
2 other person or entity authorized to request a national criminal
3 history record or an analysis of fingerprints check for commercial,
4 licensing, or other purposes, except law enforcement purposes, shall
5 conduct a national criminal history records record check on all
6 persons of the entity authorized to access or review national
7 criminal history records checks information by July 1, 2009, and
8 within sixty (60) days thereafter. National criminal history record
9 checks conducted for access and review purposes shall be completed
10 prior to the individual receiving and reviewing national criminal
11 history record information and may be conducted up to thirty (30)
12 days before the effective date of the entity’s authorization to
13 conduct national criminal history record checks.
14 3. Each agency, person, or entity authorized to request a
15 criminal history record or an analysis of fingerprints shall pay a
16 fee to the Bureau for each criminal history record or fingerprint
17 analysis as follows:
18 Oklahoma criminal history record only $15.00 $20.00 each
19 Oklahoma criminal history record with
20 fingerprint analysis $19.00 $25.00 each
21 National criminal history record with
22 fingerprint analysis submitted
23 electronically $41.00 each
24
SB1921 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 National criminal history record with
2 fingerprint analysis by mail $55.00 each
3 4. For purposes of this section, “a national criminal history
4 record check” means a check of criminal history records entailing
5 the fingerprinting of the individual and submission of the
6 fingerprints to the United States Federal Bureau of Investigation
7 (FBI) for the purpose of obtaining the national criminal history
8 record of the person from the FBI. A national criminal history
9 record check may be obtained only when a check is authorized or
10 required by state or federal law.
11 Agencies authorized by statute to conduct national criminal
12 history background checks for individuals are eligible to
13 participate in the Federal Rap Back Program administered by the
14 Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation. The Oklahoma State Bureau
15 of Investigation is authorized to submit fingerprints to the FBI Rap
16 Back System to be retained in the FBI Rap Back System for the
17 purpose of being searched by future submissions to the FBI Rap Back
18 System, including latent fingerprint searches, and to collect all
19 Federal Rap Back Program fees from eligible agencies wishing to
20 participate and remit such fees to the Federal Bureau of
21 Investigation FBI.
22 5. Unless a national criminal history record is specifically
23 requested, a fingerprint analysis shall be limited to only those
24 records available at the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation.
SB1921 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Foll owing receipt of the appropriate fee, the Bureau shall provide,
2 as soon as possible, the criminal history record requested;
3 provided, however, it shall be the duty and responsibility of the
4 requesting authority to evaluate the criminal history record as such
5 record may apply to a specific purpose or intent. An individual may
6 submit a certified court record showing that a charge was dismissed
7 or a certified copy of a gubernatorial pardon to the Oklahoma State
8 Bureau of Investigation, and upon verification of that record, the
9 Bureau records shall reflect the dismissal of that charge.
10 C. The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation may maintain an
11 identification file, including fingerprint impressions, on any
12 person under eighteen (18) years of age who is arrested or subject
13 to criminal or juvenile delinquency proceedings, provided all such
14 information shall be confidential and shall only be made available
15 to the Bureau and other law enforcement agencies. Whenever a
16 fingerprint impression or other identification information is
17 submitted to the Bureau on a person under eighteen (18) years of
18 age, the Bureau may retain and file such fingerprint and
19 identification information for identification purposes only. The
20 Bureau shall ensure that the information received and maintained for
21 identification purposes on persons under eighteen (18) years of age
22 shall be handled and processed with great care to keep such
23 information confidential from the general public. The Bureau may
24 receive and maintain the fingerprints and other identification
SB1921 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 info rmation on any person under eighteen (18) years of age believed
2 to be the subject of a runaway, missing, or abduction investigation,
3 for identification purposes at the request of a parent, guardian, or
4 legal custodian of the person.
5 D. Any person who knowingly procures, utters, or offers any
6 false, forged, or materially altered criminal history record shall
7 be guilty of a Class D1 felony offense and upon conviction shall be
8 punished by imprisonment as provided for in subsections B through F
9 of Section 20N of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes, or by a fine
10 not to exceed Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both such
11 fine and imprisonment and fine.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
